  <steps>
    <step>Re-read SPEC §4 (the decision-criteria framework) — internalize the criteria categories before applying</step>
    <step>Re-read notes/01, notes/02, notes/03 in sequence to load the inventory + feature catalog</step>
    <step>For S1 SprkChat: apply technical fit criteria (conversational? latency budget? state coupling? streaming?), apply Agent Framework value criteria (which of 10 features would S1 use?), apply migration cost criteria (rewrite scope? package impact? test impact?). Recommendation + rationale + open questions</step>
    <step>Repeat for S2 AnalysisOrchestration + JPS, S3 Builder, S4 Background AI jobs, S5 Foundry Agent Service overlap, S6 M365 Copilot, S7 Insights Engine MCP, S8 (if discovered)</step>
    <step>Use Spaarke's BFF AI extraction assessment as a tonal model — it surfaced honest "structurally AI-dominant but operationally justified" findings; this assessment should surface similarly honest conclusions even when uncomfortable</step>
    <step>Write notes/04-per-surface-decision-matrix.md — one section per surface, each with subsections: "Technical fit evaluation", "Agent Framework value", "Migration cost", "Recommendation", "Open questions for human decision". Cite notes/01-03 sections in every claim</step>
    <step>Add a closing "Recommendation summary table" — single table with columns: Surface | Recommendation | Top 2 reasons | Top open question</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(assessment): per-surface decision matrix (R1 task 004)`</step>
  </steps>
